The paper deals with load balancing in networks, which is a topic that falls under distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses different communication models and protocols, which are relevant to network engineering (cs.NE) and information theory (cs.IT). The analysis of the discrete case involves non-linear behavior and rounding errors, which are topics in scientific computing (cs.SI) and algorithms (cs.DS).
